text.tspan: Native. Feels right because it is right.

flowRoot.flowPara: Midori is a fast, slick, and modern web browser built on industry standard technologies like WebKit. But unlike many of its peers, Midori is also fully native to elementary, using the same GTK toolkit that ensures the perfect desktop compatibility and integration found in our other apps.
With its simple interface and compact AppMenu, Midori stays out of your way so you can just enjoy browsing the web. No overcrowded toolbars, statusbars, or menubars to hold you back.

text.tspan: Lightweight. Float like a feather, sting like a bee.

flowRoot.flowPara: Even thought it packs in just as many features as the big boys, Midori manages to stay light on it toes, using up less of your precious system resources. It starts faster, surfs faster, and doesn't hog your CPU.

text.tspan: Requires Ubuntu 11.10 Oneric Ocelot or later
